Seriya is just. Now staring at the crying Argenti. He speaks up for a moment. “Uh. Are you okay..???”

“There there, it has.” Seriya just slowly leans down and pats Argenti’s head.
"I have an owie on my everywhere-"
“Thats normal. Do you need anything to help your uh.....”Owies”..?” Seriya gets back up. Looking around for anything of help
"It's fine..."
“Well, since you’re still you know, hurting everywhere. I will keep you company until youre better. Deal?”
"Ok..." He smiled
“Well, since im probably going to be here with you for a while, do you wanna talk about anything?” Seriya smiled, looking over to Argenti.
"Uhh" he was at a I II II I_ for words
“Argenti are you good? Cat got your tongue?” He waved his hand infront of Argenti.
"Y-yeah kinda! maybe it's just the pain!"
“Ah, then take as much time as you need to put together your words. After all, i will be here for a bit.”
"Uhhh wanna watch TV?"
“Sure. What do you wanna watch?” Seriya gets up and is now looking for a remote. Why do these things always get lost?
He looked around for it then spotted it. "Oh hey it's on the floor." Argenti bent over to pick it up, coincidentally showing how phat his ass was.
Seriya has priorities other than ass. Like having some fun with his friend. “Oh! Good eye. Thank you Argenti.” He smiled. But inside there was a small part of him going: arghansnwnc.
He sat back down, remote in hand. "Maybe there's something on Netflix."
“Honestly, your pain your pick. I’ll just watch with you.” Seriya also sat back down. He looked really calm, but alittle happy.
"What's this? JoJo's Bizarre Adventure?"
“Hm. Sounds festive.” Seriya waves his hands around alittle.
"maybe a few episodes won't hurt."
Agrenti started the first episode. The name "Joestar" insantly struck alarms in his head, but he figured it was just a coincidence
But when the character Dio was revealed, a wave of shock hit him
“Huh. Im guessing this is just a show about the past. Its a bit disturbing seeing Dio. You alright with this Argenti?”
"It's...kind of a mindfuck...but I'm also kind of curious. What if we see Joseph when he was younger?"
“Mr.Joestar? Most likely. If this is a story about the Joestar’s bloodline.” Seriya was a bit disturbed this was a telling of the joestar’s bloodline. But at least they werent living it.
Around the third episode, the character Speedwagon introduces himself. "so wait, you're telling me THIS mugger is the founder of THE speedwagon foundation?"
“Yeeep. Amazing honestly.” During this point. Seriya has just been leaning on Argenti. Watching with him on the retelling of the joestar story.
Argenti was blushing a little, but it was barely noticeable
Eventually, they reached the 9th episode
The TV played the scene of Jonathan Joestar's death
Argenti started to cry
Seriya was now alittle concerned that they were basically invading personal affairs of the joestars, but Seriya just wrapped his arms around Argenti and just patted him.
Argenti, being the emotional himbo he is, cried into Seriya's shoulder.
"Next episode will be the last one for tonight..."
They then witness Joseph Joestar's escapades as a young man in New York
"THAT'S Joseph? He was so COOL!"
“Oh. Its not that surprising he was so rambunctious. Well, Are you alright now Argenti? No more pain?”
"Yeah...feeling a lot better."
"It's weird to know where a lot of our adventure in '88 really started."
“Yeah..i guess so. Im glad youre feeling better..” just as Seriya finishes his sentance, he falls asleep with Argenti. You should probably do something about the fire man sleeping on you Argenti.

Venor sneaks up behind the house and crouches, dragging a bag behind her. She peers round the side to see where Lamia is before standing up and leaning against the side subtly.
Lamia was suddenly right in front of her. "Hello."

Venor bites down on her lip to stop from shrieking, then shrugs it off. "Heya. I got some stuff." The bag she's carrying contains plastic wrap, bubble wrap, glue, googly eyes, pipe cleaner, and more. "I'll put the bag in the living room, that's the centerpoint for supplies, and we set as many booby traps as possible." She cracks her knuckles. "I'm going in through the window- It's fun." She does so, somehow unlocking it from the outside, and landing lightly on the floor.
"I just have toilet paper."

"Have fun. You can use my supplies too, if you want. Also, watch out for doorways, I'm putting clear wrap across them." Venor grins, and speeds off. There's a tinge of amusement to her emotions, and she's clinging to it.
"THE WORLD!" Lamia stops time to slap some googly eyes and Venor's forehead

Venor stops and laughs, happy and amused. "You joker, you." she mock growls at him. *Are my emotions coming back? How? Is this some sort of compensation?* she asks herself, then shoos the thoughts away in favour of just being happy.
Lamia was TPing Argenti's house
And also put a plush tortoise on the steps

Venor had a whole plan set up. She stuck googly eyes on everything in the fridge, glued the toilet paper rolls together, then glued the trail end of the ones being used to the full roll. She laid bubble wrap under all the carpets, and took a single cup of clear jello in a water glass out and put it on the table. Finally, she used a modified whoopee cushion that shrieked instead of lost air to put on a seat, and put clear wrap across the doorways. "Job well done."
//why is he being bullied?

Venor, finally, puts up a small camera that will cling to Argenti as he enters the house - just so they can see the result. She starts to stream it to her laptop. "Ready to see the consequences?" She asks, and jumps out the window. "This can stream from just about anywhere but still."
"I don't know where he is but yes."
"Alright." Venor conjures a small fence for them to hide behind, but just short enough that they can peer over the top if they need to. "And now, we wait." She has a devilish grin on her face.
((I'm going to assume they keep each other entertained until Argenti comes back))

"Sure! What's your idea, since I came up with the last?"
"Hmmm..."

Venor glances over. "Whatcha found?"
He unleashed The World and made sure it was in the other mun's peripheral vision
the other mun noticed. "Lord Dio?"
"PUCCI!"
"*Lord*-" Venor wheezes
They ran out and hugged each other
"Wh... Introduce me, Lamia?"

"My name is Castus." The mun introduced himself. 
"His human's name was Enrico Pucci. He was a priest Dio would ramble to about gravity and shit he thought about for 100 years."
"I have destroyed multiple universes."
"A reaper, huh? Good to meet you." Venor isn't intimidated in the slightest. "I've heard a little about you on my own missions as Bella."
"My dear friend, you have missed a lot- who are you texting?"
"I wish to find the mun called Gemi and show her a thing or 2."
"Uh. What about Gemi?" Venor leans against Lamia. "Her fiances aren't gonna be too happy about that."
"Under normal circumstances I would have GLADLY hosted their wedding. But now that I have been so...*humiliated* with the mighty plasma watching it all, I have to get an eye for an eye with Gemi."
"Oh please, the Plasma ain't watching right now, we're in the middle of a revolution." Venor rolls her eyes - Every single one of them, she's opened all of the possible eyes she has.
"a...what?"
"Oh right! the revolution! Well, muns are revolting against the plasma and I'm on the rebels side out of spite. Unless I meet an amazing and hot plasma, I'm staying there."
"The Plasma were experimenting on some of us, me included, so we're fighting them. Lamia's on the revolution side."

"I will stay by your side, Lamia."
"That would include fighting alongside Gemi."
"Lmao simp-" Venor cackles, still leaning against Lami. This is the funniest shit to her.
Castus glared at her.
Venor smiles back at him, all innocent.
White Snake takes her eyesight as a disk and then puts it back in after 10 seconds
Careless Whisper bites his ankle in fox-form.
Castus exhales through his nose
Venor smiles at him with three mouths.
"So are YOU partaking in this revolution as well?"
"Why wouldn't I? My emotions have been taken by the Plasma. I want them back. Besides, I enjoy fighting." Venor blinks slowly
"The plasma can do that?!"
*Maybe THEY are the TRUE Gods*

"Morise has... experiments." Venor shudders as fear floods her once more. "I was chained up for a few days to make me weaker, and then they took all but one of my emotions." Lamia would be able to feel that she's now leaning on him for support more than posing now.
"Oh my..." Castus seemed shocked.
"...Not that it matters, of course. I've dealt with it well." Venor puts on a brave expression, still relying on Lamia for support.
Lamia notices and does not falter
"I see..." *What other powers could the plasma possess?*
"Yeah..." Venor slowly regains her balance with Lamia's support.

"Anyways we're gonna fuck with some people. Wanna join?"
"Thanks for the offer, but I refuse.  I am still hurt from my encounter with Gemi and must rest at my house."
Castus walked off
"An... interesting person, isnt he?" Venor says, staring after him. She suddenly stands on her own. "Idontneedhelp-" she mumbles.
"Sure." Suddenly, he vanishes.
And then he's right in front of her. "Boo!"
Venor let's out a muffled curse. "Lamia!" She purses her lips, but her shoulders are shaking with controlled laughter.
Lamia smirks. "He was strange on earth, too. Just...accepting that Dio was allergic to sunlight."
"Wow. That's weird." Venor grins. "Just like... Ah yes. Allergies to sunlight. Normal."
"Weird how a vampire was able to convince a priest to work for him. Literature says vampires are repelled by holy things."

"Correct. Holy water, crosses... by all accounts he shouldn't have been able to enter a church." Venor taps her lips thoughtfully. "Though... he had the fangs, yet sucked blood from his fingers. Can you do that?"

"I still possess some vampiric abilities, but not that one." Lamia sighed. "Though thankfully, I am not weak to sunlight. Although during my times as a vampire, I wonder where that myth about vampires having no reflection and being allergic to garlic and running water came from."
"Do you still have fangs? Show me your teeth." Venor bares her own sharp teeth in a grin. "I wonder that too..."
Lamia grins, revealing distinct fangs instead of regular canines
"Nice!" Venor absentmindedly runs a finger over Lamia's fangs before retracting her hand. "And they're real."
He resisted the urge to bite her finger off
Venor grins. "Impressive." She runs her tongue over her own teeth. "You are a magnificent creature."
"What now? I mean, we could hang at my castle."
"You have a castle?! Let's get there!"
"OK!"
